<br>
Catharsis is a guild of strong Player Characters that<br>
will /duel anyone and raid cities.  The idea of<br>
good or evil is an abstract to the members of<br>
Catharsis. There will not be requirements like &quot;you<br>
have to raid Kelethin, Grobb, or Qeynos or you’re out<br>
of the guild&quot;<br>
<br>
If you want to raid a city, then do it.<br>
<br>
/duel anyone that is a jackass.<br>
<br>
The only time the guild tag will be shown publicly is<br>
during Raids, Duels (this includes the member fighting<br>
the duel, and any others that are observing as well<br>
then will again be hidden as soon as the duel is<br>
finished), or other guild sanctioned events! At all<br>
other times the guild tag will be anonymous (not<br>
shown). <br>
<br>
/target all idiots.<br>
 <br>
The primary goal of Catharsis is to create a guild<br>
that is as feared, as it is desired, envied as well as<br>
respected. The focus of the guild is to level its<br>
members to no less than 52 seasons so that maximum<br>
participation of major and worthwhile raids is<br>
optimized and realized.<br>
<br>
/attack stupidity.<br>
<br>
This is a guild of purging, a cleansing of all that is<br>
intolerable from the annoying to the frustrating, to<br>
make Norrath an enjoyable experience for all who are<br>
brave enough to venture across its borders!<br>
<br>
/claim your victory!<br>
<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong><br>
<!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="font-size:large;">Above all else, adhere to the rules set forth by SOE.  Failure to comply with those rules will result in EXPULSION!</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--></strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Rules to die by</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
 <br>
1)&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Only show your guild tag during a raid, a duel or an aid station<br>
2)&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp /Duel all Jackasses you meet<br>
3)&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Settle your differences by /duel, if that does not bring finality, my judgment is absolute<br>
4)&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Need before greed<br>
5)&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp No profit is to be made from another member, reimbursement for expenses may be required, (e.g. Sow potion may not be free, but only the cost of making it be collected)<br>
6)&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp No /hug, /kiss, /grabass, /looser-emotes in guild chat.  I will kill you myself if you do.<br>
7)&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Never KS another person, if they piss you off, /duel them.<br>
<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 8) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/glasses.gif ALT="8)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp It is okay to attack any city you see fit.<br>
9)&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Do not bully other people; bullying is a sign of weakness and lack of confidence in your abilities.<br>
10)&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp If at any time you do not like what is happening within the guild, leave.  No last parting words, no tear-jerking woe, just leave.  This guild may not be what you are looking for, you could be happier someplace else.  It’s okay, that’s just how life works in all aspects.<br>
<br>
<br>
Contact Blackroot, Kugel, Garioch, or Tazmin for more info<br>
